webpackJsonp([62720123088807],{344:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>I bought this <a href="http://yrmichael.com">domain</a> about 2 months ago. It was intended to be a personal site of sorts, to make it easier for me to share the stuff I build.</p>\n<p>Yet, for some reason, I never got round to making my personal site. (Till now.) Well, I could attribute this delay to my finals and being busy with other stuff. But the truth is, I didn\'t really want to. I procrastinated. I was lazy.</p>\n<!--more-->\n<p>I was afraid of being judged. That once I made something, it would define me. More so a personal site. As a result, I simply set my nodejs server to respond to any http requests with the request object.</p>\n<p>This was what visitors would see:</p>\n<p><img src="/static/img/blog/oldsite.jpg" alt="worst than crappy page"></p>\n<p>If a crappy personal site was bad. This just screams "I can\'t be bothered to write some markup, so here is something completely useless."</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>When you donâ€™t create things, you become defined by your tastes rather than ability. Your tastes only narrow and exclude people. so create. <div>- <cite>_why the Lucky Stiff</cite></div></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So here it is. Me doing better. Me reminding myself of the joys of coding. The reasons that I started to code in the first place.</p>\n<p>Keep hacking.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Remembering why I code",date:"07 June, 2012"},fields:{slug:"/2012/06/07/remembering-why-i-code.html"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/2012/06/07/remembering-why-i-code.html"}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---2012-06-07-remembering-why-i-code-html-0099c9fbd4c90e61eced.js.map